# Vintage Cameras Marketplace — Claude Code Primer

> This file lives at `.kilo/contracts/CLAUDE.md`. Any fresh Claude Code (or
> compatible agentic) session should read it first. It is generated from
> `agent-spec.yaml` + `task-graph.yaml` and is the single source of truth
> for "what we are building, why, and what shape proof must take."
>
> Cross-references: see `CONTRACT_KIT_CREATOR_ANCHORS.md` for the 7 anchors
> this kit enforces; this file pertains primarily to **Anchor 1** (Agentic
> Software Engineering).

---

## Project intent

A marketplace where collectors list, browse, and buy vintage film cameras.
Listings carry condition grading, sample photos, and serviceable status.
Buyers can message sellers, place offers, and pay through escrow. The
product must look credible to serious collectors and protect both sides
from fraud.

## Domain & audience

- **Domain pack:** `marketplace`
- **Primary audiences:** engineering, exec, legal, design

## Authoritative artifacts

| File | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `agent-spec.yaml` | Machine-readable spec (REQ-, ADR-, RISK- ids). |
| `task-graph.yaml` | DAG of buildable tasks. Claim by `id`. |
| `verification/INDEX.md` | Map of acceptance criteria to executable tests + Playwright traces. |
| `risk-register/owasp-llm.md` | OWASP LLM Top 10 mapping (if/when AI is added). |
| `compliance/ssdf-attestation.md` | NIST SSDF practice coverage. |
| `.github/workflows/release.yml` | SLSA L3 + cosign release. |

If you change behavior, also update the relevant artifact above. Drift
between code and these files is treated as a build break.

## Capabilities you must respect (REQ-XXX)

- **REQ-001** — Sellers create listings (>=3 photos, condition grade required).
- **REQ-002** — Catalog search under 300ms p95 with brand synonyms.
- **REQ-003** — Offers with 72-hour expiry.
- **REQ-004** — Escrowed payments with 7-day auto-release.
- **REQ-005** — Buyer-seller messaging with PII redaction.
- **REQ-006** — Trust signals (verified badge, reputation, history).
- **REQ-007** — Admin moderation queue with immutable audit log.

Every PR description MUST cite at least one REQ id (or ADR/RISK id) so
the gate `proof.req-id-cited` passes.

## Standing decisions (ADR-XXXX)

- **ADR-0001** — Stripe Connect for escrowed payments (accepted).
- **ADR-0002** — Postgres + Meilisearch for catalog search (accepted).
- **ADR-0003** — Cloudflare R2 for image storage (accepted).
- **ADR-0004** — No crypto payment rails in v1 (accepted — do not relitigate).

If you propose changing one of these, open a new ADR superseding the
prior; do not silently swap implementations.

## Risk posture (RISK-XXX)

- **RISK-001** Counterfeit listings (high/high).
- **RISK-002** Payment fraud / chargebacks (medium/critical).
- **RISK-003** Off-platform leakage (medium/high).
- **RISK-004** Image-storage cost runaway (low/high).
- **RISK-005** Dispute brigading via fake reviews (medium/medium).

When you implement code that touches any of these surfaces (image upload,
messaging, escrow, reviews, listing moderation) cite the relevant RISK
id in your commit body and the relevant test.

## How to claim work

1. Read `task-graph.yaml`. Pick a task whose `dependsOn` items are all
   `done`. Tasks are uniquely identified by `T-XXX`.
2. Announce in the PR body: `Claiming T-007 (Search API with brand-synonym
   dictionary). Satisfies REQ-002.`
3. Implement. Add tests under `verification/` mapped to the acceptance
   criteria of the task.
4. Run `npm run check && npm run test && npm run e2e`. Trace artifacts
   from Playwright must land under `verification/e2e/.traces/` (Anchor 3).
5. Update the row in `verification/INDEX.md` so non-coders can review.

## Style & guardrails

- TypeScript end-to-end. No JS files.
- Public APIs are typed via tRPC; do not introduce raw REST endpoints
  without an ADR.
- Never log raw user payment data. Stripe IDs only.
- Never echo API keys or secrets in generated code, comments, or test
  fixtures (gate: `compliance.no-secrets-in-output`).
- Use `must` / `shall` / `will` only when the sentence cites a REQ or
  ADR id. Unscoped imperative claims are flagged by `proof.req-id-cited`.

## Definition of "done" for any task

A task is done when **all** of:

- All acceptance criteria from the matching capability are exercised by
  at least one executable test (Anchor 2).
- Playwright trace exists if the task touches a buyer- or seller-facing
  flow (Anchor 3).
- CI is green: lint, typecheck, unit, e2e, scorecard.
- The PR description cites the relevant REQ-, ADR-, or RISK- ids.

If you cannot honor one of the above, stop and post a question rather
than ship a half-met contract.
